comment: An absolute oak monster. Not a pleasant tasting experience for me.
Nose is sweet with a hint of spice. Starts out a little flat but finishes strong with a peppery note. Hints of leather and oil. Surprised at the strong strong taste given the proof.
10/12/19 Beer Bourbon & BBQ fest in Leesburg
A bit  too much burn for my tastes.  Smells like a cheap bourbon.

Nose: sweet corn, light vanilla and slight spice 

Palate: faint all across the board...  slight sweetness, spice and warming the ethanol taste

Finish: ethanol warmth and spice 

Only good as a well bourbon to add to a cocktail because of the proof, lacks real flavor
Very sweet fruit scent and initial flavor with strong spicy finish.

Vanilla and spice on the nose.

Very strong oak taste followed by a harsh alcohol burn
Strong corn / grain/ Karo corn syrup on the nose and palate. A lot of alcohol burn and bitterness on the palate. Better whiskeys for the price.
I tried this back in college at the rugby house.  The taste of it knocked me on my ass harder than the team prop could!
